We will rebuild our World. 

But for now, let's protect it.

I remain optimistic about one thing only: 

Ukrainians are unstoppable. ğŸ‡ºğŸ‡¦

Whatever happens next, you will have 44 million angry and determined people.

2/ Donate.

Ukrainian army and volunteers need your help.

https://t.co/vASUbmd61R

1/ Spread awareness.

I'm shocked how many people still think it is a couple of attacks next to the border. 

The fight is happening in the capital and all around the country.

Please share.

Now the most crucial part:

How YOU can help in 2 simple steps:

They notice the barbaric attack on the free nation.

They notice missiles targeted at hospitals, schools, and apartment buildings.

They notice Ukraine is staying strong and united against the enemy.

They notice where this might go next if they don't interfere.
And now, three days later, the World starts to notice.

Ukrainian President. My god. 

This guy is a Leader I never expected him to become. 

He is on the front line.

Ukrainian citizens are volunteering in the local self-defense units. 

They run out of ammunition to give to them. 

Ukrainians abroad are coordinating help for refugees or people trying to get back.

It is not an equal fight. 

We are fighting a nuclear country.

But we are also not equal in spirit. 

Ukrainian spirit is all-time-high.

Russian spirit is based on fact-less propaganda that breaks right after seeing the resistance.

Three days later, we still stay strong.

Russian army got the resistance they didn't expect.

The World was sending us "thoughts and prayers."

Everyone thought Ukraine brought a knife to a gunfight.

But apart from the knife, Ukraine has balls of steel.

putin thought he would occupy our capital, Kyiv, within the first day.

aka Blitzkrieg 2.0

He enjoys drawing his inspirations from his buddy, hitler.
First, I want to say that I'm so fucking proud of every Ukrainian, and especially our Military!
